title: Liverpool, Chelsea & Moussa Dembele: Rumours get crazy
text:
Liverpool, Chelsea & Moussa Dembele: Rumours get crazy By Benjamin Newman on Tuesday, January 31, 2017 Liverpool, Chelsea & Moussa Dembele 
The rumour of Tuesday on transfer deadline day concerned claims Chelsea were making a late move for star Celtic forward Moussa Dembele. 
Fuelled by the sighting of Dembele on his way to London the story kept on snowballing, that was until the striker turned to social media to make it crystal clear that he was staying put at Celtic. 
But since it’s become clear that Dembele isn’t joining Antonio Conte’s men, another, hugely conflicting narrative is also taking hold involving Liverpool. Rumours get crazy 
Journalist Ian McGarry has posted a whole different claims on social media, claiming that Chelsea were never interested in signing the French forward. 
Instead, it’s claimed that Liverpool were the big Premier League club who tried to land the Celtic striker. 
Jurgen Klopp was rebuffed twice in his efforts to land Brendan Rodgers’ star. 
McGarry finally claimed that two other unnamed clubs tried to sign Dembele. 
Who to believe? #Celtic rejected bid from #LFC and enquiries from two other clubs for Dembele. There was no interest from Chelsea. #CFC . 
— Ian McGarry (@garbosj) January 31, 2017 Loading tags...
